180 grams Prawns
1 unit(s) Ginger
300 grams Udon Noodles
1 unit(s) Lime
2 sachet(s) Hoisin Sauce
2 unit(s) Garlic
1 unit(s) Onion
1 sachet(s) Soy Sauce
1 unit(s) Courgette
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Water
to taste Oil

Peel and grate the garlic (or use a garlic press).
Peel and grate the ginger (use a teaspoon to easily scrape away the peel).
Halve, peel and thinly slice the onion.
Chop the lime into 4 wedges.
Trim the courgette then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Place a pan over high heat (without oil).
When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, 6-8 mins.
Stir only every so often—this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour.
Once cooked, season with salt and pepper.

Lower the heat to medium-high.
Add the prawns, garlic, ginger and onion to the pan with a drizzle of oil.
Fry until onion is softened and prawns are cooked, stirring regularly, 4-5 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Carefully separate the noodles.
Add them to the pan with the prawns.
Cook until warmed through, 1-2 mins.

Add the hoisin sauce and soy sauce to the pan.
Carefully toss everything together to coat in the sauce.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and lime juice.
TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs loosening.

Divide the saucy prawn noodles between plates or bowls.
Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside.